          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                                        <date>April 17. 1852</date>.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Valued Friend!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">If I am not mistaken<lb/> I am indebted to you a
                                        reply to your<lb/> esteemed favour of the <date>12th
                                                  March</date>, the con-<lb/>tents of which was duly
                                        noted, and in reply<lb/> regret that any act of mine should
                                        have<lb/> proven any wise detrimental to your interest,<lb/>
                                        I know (that your good knowledge of) Ger-<lb/>man (Bavarian)
                                        liberality in patronizing a<lb/> Journal could not have been
                                        much im-<lb/>paired by the publication of the article
                                        con-<lb/>cerning the "Beth Haim" I can assure<lb/> you that
                                        it did not make one jot<lb/> difference. I have noticed all
                                        your<lb/> hints concerning the congregation and hope<lb/> to
                                        profit by them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I see by the letter that <persName>Jacob A.
                                                  Levy</persName><lb/> recd from you the other day,
                                        that you<lb/> anticipate a flare up with the Education<lb/>
                                        Society, whilst I know that you main-<lb/>tain correct views
                                        and a stickler of<lb/> just principles, I must advise you,
                                        to<lb/> desist the opposition to the majority,<lb/> rather
                                        retire <sic>peacably</sic> from them than<lb/> to combat
                                        with your superior in power,</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>I wish I could see you otherwise situated<lb/> with the Israelites
                                        of <placeName>Philada</placeName>. I fear from<lb/> what I
                                        can learn that the breach of<lb/>
                                        <sic>dissention</sic> is expanding between you and<lb/>
                                        them. I have stuck to your views and<lb/> opposition here
                                        and would that I was a<lb/> member of "Mickval Israel" to
                                        stand<lb/> by you there.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Our new Hefra are about getting<lb/>
                                        <persName>Isaac Lyon</persName> to print their constitution
                                        and<lb/> it will require some Hebrew type, but<lb/> he has a
                                        parcel a proof of which I en-<lb/>close with the size of the
                                        type, they lack<lb/> the <add>ן, ץ, ף, ך, ם, ל, ט</add> to
                                        wit the <add>ל</add><lb/>
                                        <add>ט</add> all the final letters and the stops<lb/> I
                                        should like you to send me about<lb/> 12 of each of the
                                        above if you can<lb/> get them which will complete the lot<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> has in case you cannot<lb/>
                                        get them, he wants you to get a<lb/> small font of <hi
                                                  rend="underline">small pica</hi> say to the<lb/>
                                        amount of two or three dollars, if<lb/> you can get the size
                                        like the sample<lb/> he would rather have them, whatever<lb/>
                                        <sic>expence</sic> may attend the execution of<lb/> this
                                        order <persName>Mr Mailert</persName> will forward<lb/> to
                                        you, nothing more but remain as<lb/> ever yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">Jacob Ezekiel</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
